# CODEOWNERS — THE-529
#
# This file ROUTES review, it does not GATE merges. There is currently one maintainer, so a
# required-reviewer branch rule would auto-request review from whoever opened the PR and block
# every merge. Deliberately not doing that; revisit if a second maintainer joins.
#
# What it is for, today:
#   1. A machine-readable statement of which paths carry security or data-loss risk, for
#      contributors AND for coding agents working in this repo (several PRs here are agent-authored).
#   2. Correct review routing the moment there is more than one maintainer, with no archaeology
#      needed to work out what should have been watched.
#   3. A visible marker on PRs touching auth/ACL/release — the same reason the gitleaks and
#      vault-leak jobs exist: make the risky diff obvious rather than hoping a reader notices.

* @suavecito585

# --- Authentication -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Token verification. A rejection here that reports the wrong reason hid a 5-day outage (THE-520);
# a rejection that wrongly PASSES is an authentication bypass.
